    <!-- ══ CH 1: THE BEGINNING ══ -->
    <div class="story-section bg-a" id="ss1">
      <div class="story-section-inner">

        <div class="ch-opener rv">
          <p class="ch-opener-eyebrow">Chapter One</p>
          <h2 class="ch-opener-title" style="color:#7ab0ff">The Boy Who Was<br>"Just A Classmate"</h2>
          <p class="ch-opener-meta">September 4, 2025</p>
        </div>

        <div class="narrator-block rv">
          <span class="narrator-em">🧑</span>
          <p class="narrator-text">I'll be honest. When I first texted her, I wasn't thinking about love. I wasn't thinking about butterflies or late-night calls or nicknames that would turn into an entire dessert menu. I was thinking about attendance. <span class="hi">Just attendance.</span></p>
          <p class="narrator-aside">— Chaitanya, looking back</p>
        </div>

        <div class="chat-window rv">
          <div class="chat-date">04 September 2025 · 11:40 AM · Day 1</div>
          <div class="cb cbl"><span class="cbn">Chaitanya</span>Class me hai kya ???</div>
          <div class="cb cbr"><span class="cbn">Khushi</span>yesss</div>
          <div class="cb cbl"><span class="cbn">Chaitanya</span>Sir hai ?? Attendance laga de..<br>Chaitanya — 2501060086</div>
          <div class="cb cbr"><span class="cbn">Khushi</span>okiii</div>
          <div class="cb cbl"><span class="cbn">Chaitanya</span>No problem</div>
        </div>

        <div class="narrator-block rv">
          <p class="narrator-text">She said "okiii" and I said "no problem." That was it. A roll number and a thank you that almost didn't happen. I had no idea that this girl — the one covering my attendance — was going to become the most important person in my entire world. <span class="hi">Funny how that works.</span></p>
        </div>

        <div class="scene-card rv">
          <div class="sc-label">What Chaitanya didn't know yet</div>
          <div class="sc-title" style="color:#7ab0ff">She Was Already Curious 👀</div>
          <p class="sc-body">A few hours later that same day, she asked <strong>"kl aayegaaa ???"</strong> He replied he'd come if his friends did. She said "okiii okii" — and immediately he asked <strong>"Tum aaoge??"</strong> She said she'd asked because she wanted to know if he'd be there. He told her to come. She said okieeeee. <strong>And neither of them realised this was already something.</strong></p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ══ CH 2: "I LOVE U AS A FRIEND" ══ -->
    <div class="story-section bg-b" id="ss2">
      <div class="story-section-inner">

        <div class="ch-opener rv">
          <p class="ch-opener-eyebrow">Chapter Two</p>
          <h2 class="ch-opener-title" style="color:#ff9ab8">"I Love U As A Friend" 😂<br><span style="font-size:.6em;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;color:rgba(255,154,184,0.6)">The most unconvincing sentence ever typed</span></h2>
          <p class="ch-opener-meta">September 9–20, 2025</p>
        </div>

        <div class="narrator-block rv">
          <span class="narrator-em">🧑</span>
          <p class="narrator-text">Within days, we were talking every evening. She was telling me I was a <span class="hi">"bandaa achaa"</span> and I was pretending not to care. She called me a yapper — someone who talks too much — and honestly, she wasn't wrong. But here's the thing about Khushi: she could out-yap me any day of the week. And I loved every single word.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="chat-window rv">
          <div class="chat-date">09 September 2025 · 8:00 PM</div>
          <div class="cb cbr"><span class="cbn">Khushi</span>tuu bndaa achaa h vaaisee 🥹🫷🏻</div>
          <div class="cb cbl"><span class="cbn">Chaitanya</span>Vo muje pata hai. Kuch naya batao</div>
          <div class="cb cbr"><span class="cbn">Khushi</span>i lovee u bolde theen 😭</div>
          <div class="cb cbl"><span class="cbn">Chaitanya</span>I LOVE U AS A FRIEND 💞💞</div>
          <div class="cb cbr"><span class="cbn">Khushi</span>i love h as aa bff 👉🏻👈🏻</div>
        </div>

        <div class="pull-quote rv">
          <p class="pq-text">"Depression kuch nahi hota... Bolo. Koi judge kare toh vo uski problem hai."</p>
          <p class="pq-attr">— Chaitanya to Khushi, Day 6 · The moment she knew he was different</p>
        </div>

        <div class="narrator-block rv">
          <p class="narrator-text">She had told me she gets quiet in class, that she feels like she'll go into depression if she stays silent. And I said — without thinking — <span class="hi">"Depression kuch nahi hota. Bolo. Koi judge kare toh vo uski problem hai."</span> I don't know why I said it so easily. Maybe because even then, without fully knowing it, <span class="hi">I wanted her to feel safe.</span></p>
        </div>

        <div class="chat-window rv">
          <div class="chat-date">09 September 2025 · 8:22 PM · The Yapper Moment</div>
          <div class="cb cbr"><span class="cbn">Khushi</span>mrkeo bss bkk bkk krne se mtlb hotaa h 🥹</div>
          <div class="cb cbl"><span class="cbn">Chaitanya</span>Yapper... Nahi hota bass imagination hai. Be positive.</div>
          <div class="cb cbr"><span class="cbn">Khushi</span>🫷🏻🫷🏻🥹 yess yess</div>
        </div>

        <div class="narrator-block rv">
          <p class="narrator-text">And then she said: <span class="hi">"bndi h terrii??"</span> — asking if I had a girlfriend. I told her I was single. She got curious. She said she'd follow me around until I told her. <span class="hi">She's been following me around ever since. Just not because of that anymore.</span></p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ══ CH 3: THE PROPOSAL ══ -->
    <div class="story-section bg-d" id="ss3">
      <div class="story-section-inner">

        <div class="ch-opener rv">
          <p class="ch-opener-eyebrow">Chapter Three</p>
          <h2 class="ch-opener-title" style="color:#ff9ab8">Seventeen Days.<br>One Chaotic Confession.</h2>
          <p class="ch-opener-meta">September 21, 2025 · 5:54 PM</p>
        </div>

        <div class="narrator-block rv">
          <span class="narrator-em">🌸</span>
          <p class="narrator-text">We had been talking for exactly 17 days. Seventeen days of good mornings that weren't called good mornings yet, of teasing each other about exams, of her calling me a yapper and me secretly keeping every message. I don't even know how we got to what happened next. <span class="hi">Nobody planned it. That's the truest thing about it.</span></p>
        </div>

        <div class="chat-window rv" style="max-width:440px">
          <div class="chat-date">21 September 2025 · 5:54 PM · The Proposal That Made No Sense</div>
          <div class="cb cbl"><span class="cbn">Chaitanya</span>Propose kario phele..</div>
          <div class="cb cbr"><span class="cbn">Khushi</span>kaaisee 😭</div>
          <div class="cb cbl"><span class="cbn">Chaitanya</span>Flowers dio.. Aur accept ho gaya tho kya karigi? 🌸</div>
          <div class="cb cbr"><span class="cbn">Khushi</span>m kushii kushii accept krlungii 🥹🫷🏻</div>
          <div class="cb cbl"><span class="cbn">Chaitanya</span>Aap ki beti ne propose kiya hai.. Reject kar du?? 😏</div>
          <div class="cb cbr"><span class="cbn">Khushi</span>aaab m ni krriiii 🙂😭</div>
          <div class="cb cbl"><span class="cbn">Chaitanya</span>Muje tho passand hai.. App bato ab 🥺</div>
        </div>

        <div class="narrator-block rv">
          <p class="narrator-text">Read it again. Nobody technically proposed. Nobody technically said yes. We went in circles, we teased each other, we both pretended we weren't serious — and somehow in the middle of all that beautiful chaos, <span class="hi">we became us.</span> That's the most Khushi thing I can imagine.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="pull-quote rv" style="border-left-color:#7ab0ff">
          <p class="pq-text" style="color:#c0d8ff">"Muje tho passand hai.. App bato ab 🥺"</p>
          <p class="pq-attr">— Chaitanya · Five words that changed everything · 21 Sept 2025 · 5:54 PM</p>
        </div>

        <div class="scene-card rv">
          <div class="sc-label">What happened next</div>
          <div class="sc-title" style="color:#ff9ab8">The Nickname That Started It All 🍮</div>
          <p class="sc-body">That same night, within hours, she was already calling him <strong>bbu</strong>. He said "Ok my bbuuu 🩵." She shot back "nii horiii meree bbbuu." Then he told her he'd gone to get rasmalai but hadn't brought her any. She was outraged. He laughed. <strong>The word "rasmalai" would follow them for 10 months and counting.</strong></p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ══ CH 4: MONTH BY MONTH ══ -->
    <div class="story-section bg-a" id="ss4">
      <div class="story-section-inner">

        <div class="ch-opener rv">
          <p class="ch-opener-eyebrow">Chapter Four</p>
          <h2 class="ch-opener-title">Ten Months.<br>Ten Stories.</h2>
          <p class="ch-opener-meta">September 2025 → June 2026</p>
        </div>

        <div class="narrator-block rv">
          <span class="narrator-em">🧑</span>
          <p class="narrator-text">People think love is made of grand moments. I used to think that too. But looking back at 10 months of messages — <span class="hig">132,000 of them</span> — I realise love is actually made of small, consistent, ordinary things. Let me take you through it, month by month.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- SEPTEMBER -->
        <div class="month-divider rv"><div class="md-line"></div><div class="md-label">🌸 September 2025</div><div class="md-line"></div></div>
        <div class="scene-card rv" style="border-color:rgba(255,154,184,.18)">
          <div class="sc-label">Month 1 · The beginning</div>
          <div class="sc-title" style="color:#ff9ab8">The Month We Found Each Other</div>
          <p class="sc-body">It all happened so fast. September 4 — first message. September 9 — "I love u as a friend" (liar 😭). September 21 — the world's most chaotic proposal. By the end of the month, she was texting me at 6 AM when something felt off, and I was texting her "tune kha liya?" every single evening like clockwork. <strong>In 27 days, we went from strangers to us.</strong> That's the September miracle.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="chat-window rv">
          <div class="chat-date">25 September 2025</div>
          <div class="cb cbl"><span class="cbn">Chaitanya</span>Nahi tere bina koi team nahi. Tere bina koi event start nahi karunga 🥺</div>
          <div class="cb cbr"><span class="cbn">Khushi</span>im bimaarr 🤧</div>
          <div class="cb cbl"><span class="cbn">Chaitanya</span>Apke sapne mai kar duga pure.. Get well soon bbu</div>
        </div>

        <!-- OCTOBER -->
        <div class="month-divider rv"><div class="md-line"></div><div class="md-label">🍂 October 2025</div><div class="md-line"></div></div>
        <div class="scene-card rv">
          <div class="sc-label">Month 2 · The 6 AM era begins</div>
          <div class="sc-title" style="color:#f5c842">The Month She Woke Me Up At 6 AM</div>
          <p class="sc-body">October 1st, 6:02 AM. I had slept at 4 AM. She texted: "bbuu." Then: "aaraa h yh niii." She hadn't said good morning, hadn't asked how I was. She just reached out, just to check. I grumbled. She laughed and said sorry. <strong>She'd been waking up just to reach me. I didn't know it then. I know it now.</strong></p>
        </div>
        <div class="chat-window rv">
          <div class="chat-date">07 October 2025</div>
          <div class="cb cbl"><span class="cbn">Chaitanya</span>Mai kya karta tere bina.. 🥺</div>
          <div class="cb cbr"><span class="cbn">Khushi</span>bssss i miss uuu</div>
          <div class="cb cbl"><span class="cbn">Chaitanya</span>I miss u more..</div>
        </div>

        <!-- NOVEMBER -->
        <div class="month-divider rv"><div class="md-line"></div><div class="md-label">❄️ November 2025</div><div class="md-line"></div></div>
        <div class="scene-card rv" style="border-color:rgba(122,176,255,.18)">
          <div class="sc-label">Month 3 · The deep feelings hit</div>
          <div class="sc-title" style="color:#7ab0ff">The Month I Realised How Much</div>
          <p class="sc-body">November 1st. I sent her a morning message before she was even awake: <strong>"Tune pyar hi itna kiya ki itne din ki sari thakan release hogi.. Love u soo sooo much."</strong> Her love wasn't loud or dramatic. It was quiet and consistent. It was in the Python notes she stayed up till midnight to make for me. <strong>The month I really understood what she meant to me.</strong></p>
        </div>
        <div class="chat-window rv">
          <div class="chat-date">08 November 2025</div>
          <div class="cb cbl"><span class="cbn">Chaitanya</span>Jab tu mere pass nahi hoti na, mai tab teri choti chiti baat pe gussa ho jata hu.. kuki I miss u.</div>
          <div class="cb cbr"><span class="cbn">Khushi</span>miss u too bbbuu 💙</div>
          <div class="cb cbl"><span class="cbn">Chaitanya</span>Nahi tu janti hi nahi mai kitna miss karta hu..</div>
        </div>

        <!-- DECEMBER -->
        <div class="month-divider rv"><div class="md-line"></div><div class="md-label">🎄 December 2025</div><div class="md-line"></div></div>
        <div class="scene-card rv">
          <div class="sc-label">Month 4 · Christmas &amp; missing her</div>
          <div class="sc-title" style="color:#5de890">The Month She Asked For A Gift</div>
          <p class="sc-body">December 25th. She texted "gifttt meraaa aaajkaaa 🎁." He asked what she wanted. She said: <strong>"jo merii princess dede 👉🏻👈🏻."</strong> He said earbuds. She said "hawww dbundhe hi nii." He laughed. Meanwhile he was already writing: <strong>"apka katna miss kara huu."</strong> The month of warm December evenings spent wishing she was closer.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- NEW YEAR -->
        <div class="month-divider rv"><div class="md-line"></div><div class="md-label">🎆 December 31 → January 1, 2026</div><div class="md-line"></div></div>
        <div class="pull-quote rv" style="border-left-color:var(--gold)">
          <p class="pq-text" style="color:#f5e0b0">"God gave me the perfect gift this year 🎁✨. And u did everything for me. Love u aur ab tho words bhi nahi hai. Thank you for treating me like a princess."</p>
          <p class="pq-attr">— Chaitanya to Khushi · 01 January 2026 · 12:49 AM</p>
        </div>
        <div class="chat-window rv">
          <div class="chat-date">01 January 2026 · 12:48 AM · Happy New Year</div>
          <div class="cb cbr"><span class="cbn">Khushi</span>hpppiestt new year bbbu 🩵🧿</div>
          <div class="cb cbl"><span class="cbn">Chaitanya</span>Happy new yearrrrrr Princesses ✨🩵</div>
          <div class="cb cbl"><span class="cbn">Chaitanya</span>God gave me the perfect gift this yearrr 🎁✨</div>
          <div class="cb cbl"><span class="cbn">Chaitanya</span>Love u aur ab tho words bhi nahi hai 🤧</div>
          <div class="cb cbl"><span class="cbn">Chaitanya</span>Ready for 2026 to create more cute and memorable moments with u 💕</div>
        </div>
        <div class="narrator-block rv">
          <p class="narrator-text">I typed that at 12:49 AM. She had already sent her New Year message at 12:09 and I had missed it — asleep. When I woke up and saw it, I sent her that paragraph. I said "love u aur ab tho words bhi nahi hai." <span class="hi">And I meant every syllable.</span></p>
        </div>

        <!-- JANUARY -->
        <div class="month-divider rv"><div class="md-line"></div><div class="md-label">❄️ January 2026</div><div class="md-line"></div></div>
        <div class="scene-card rv">
          <div class="sc-label">Month 5 · The cold month, warm conversations</div>
          <div class="sc-title" style="color:#7ab0ff">January: Still Here. Still Us.</div>
          <p class="sc-body">January came and nothing changed — except everything felt more settled. More certain. She would still message him before the bus to college. He would still check if she ate. <strong>The morning routine had become ritual.</strong> They had learned each other — the rhythms, the silences, the patterns of the other person.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- MARCH-APRIL -->
        <div class="month-divider rv"><div class="md-line"></div><div class="md-label">🌸 March → April 2026</div><div class="md-line"></div></div>
        <div class="scene-card rv">
          <div class="sc-label">Month 7–8 · Exam season, still together</div>
          <div class="sc-title" style="color:#ff9ab8">March-April: Papers and Python and Us</div>
          <p class="sc-body">Exam season hit hard. She stayed up solving Python practicals. He sent adjacency list implementations and DSA notes at 9 AM. She asked brain-related project name suggestions. He shared resources. <strong>They became each other's study partners, support systems, and midnight sanity checks.</strong></p>
        </div>

        <!-- MAY-JUNE -->
        <div class="month-divider rv"><div class="md-line"></div><div class="md-label">☀️ May → June 2026</div><div class="md-line"></div></div>
        <div class="scene-card rv">
          <div class="sc-label">Month 9–10 · Still going, still us</div>
          <div class="sc-title" style="color:var(--gold)">June: And Still, Every Morning</div>
          <p class="sc-body">June 1st, 6:03 AM: <strong>"gudmrngg bbbbu. Uthhhjaooo. ni toh bus nikl jaygiii."</strong> He replied at 6:40: "Gud morning. Babyy." Ten months in. She was still waking up early to make sure he didn't miss his bus. He was still worried she'd eaten. She was still "mines rasmalai." He was still "loce u moreee." <strong>Some things don't change. The best things never do.</strong></p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ══ CH 5: WHAT MAKES THEM THEM ══ -->
