        <div class="scene-card rv">
          <div class="sc-label">What Chaitanya wants Khushi to know · 01</div>
          <div class="sc-title">You changed what "ordinary" means to me</div>
          <p class="sc-body">Before you, I thought love had to be big. Dramatic. A grand gesture, a perfect moment. Then you came along and made a Tuesday at 6 AM feel like something worth getting up for. You asked "aaraa h yh niii?" and somehow that mattered more than anything beautiful I had read or watched. <strong>You made the ordinary extraordinary just by being in it.</strong></p>
        </div>

        <div class="scene-card rv">
          <div class="sc-label">What Chaitanya wants Khushi to know · 02</div>
          <div class="sc-title">I miss you in a way I can't explain</div>
          <p class="sc-body">"Jab tu mere pass nahi hoti na, mai tab teri choti chiti baat pe gussa ho jata hu kuki I miss u." I wrote that in November. I still mean it. When you're not there, everything feels slightly off — like a song missing one instrument. <strong>You are the part of the day I look forward to. Every day. Even the annoying ones where you call me mandak.</strong></p>
        </div>

        <div class="scene-card rv">
          <div class="sc-label">What Chaitanya wants Khushi to know · 03</div>
          <div class="sc-title">You are my best friend, not just my girlfriend</div>
          <p class="sc-body">I said it on June 14th — "Tu sirf meri girlfriend nahi hai, tu meri best friend bhi hai." And I didn't plan to say it. It came out because it was true. <strong>You're the first person I want to tell things to. Good things, bad things, the thing that happened on the way to college, the stupid thought I had at 2 AM. You are my person.</strong></p>
        </div>

        <div class="scene-card rv">
          <div class="sc-label">What Chaitanya wants Khushi to know · 04</div>
          <div class="sc-title">You made 2025 the best year of my life</div>
          <p class="sc-body">At 12:49 AM on New Year's, I wrote: <strong>"God gave me the perfect gift this year."</strong> That was you. You took 2025 — which was supposed to be just first year of college — and turned it into the year I fell in love with my best friend. I don't have words for that. I just have "loce u moreee."</p>
        </div>

        <div class="narrator-block rv">
          <span class="narrator-em">🧑</span>
          <p class="narrator-text">Khushi — you call me mandak and rasmalai and gulabjamun and babbabie. You say "no phones aab jaao" and then text three more times. You make Python notes at midnight and don't tell me until morning. You check if I ate before you check if I'm okay. <span class="hi">You are the kind of person who makes the people around them better without even trying.</span> And on your birthday, I just want you to know — you made me better. You really did. 💙</p>
        </div>

